1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:11,900
<i> You should be scared</i>

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:14,233
<i>because I'll take back
everything I lost.</i>

3
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:20,200
<i>Don't cry if they push you
away like you did to them.</i>

4
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:23,567
<i>Jade's lover is the one helping
Emma?</i>

5
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>I started to shiver
as if I was nervous.</i>

6
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:30,667
<i>She saw Emma in a bar.
She's already with someone else.</i>

7
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,067
<i>You know what? This is not true!</i>

8
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,300
<i> Love, what are you doing?</i>

9
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:37,467
<i>You will think about nothing
but us.</i>

10
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:40,300
<i>- Danilo.
- Wait.</i>

11
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:41,167
<i> Dan!</i>

12
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>- Dan.
- Can you please stop?</i>

13
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,267
<i> Dan, wait. Let's talk first.</i>

14
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,267
<i> Why did you go with that man?</i>

15
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,967
<i>You have no one to take back
and no one to come back to.</i>

16
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,467
<i>You better enjoy yourself
with your lover!</i>

17
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,500
<i> Dan.</i>

18
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:54,467
<i>- Dan, wait. Let's talk.
- No!</i>

19
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:47,733
Darn it, Emma.

20
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:48,400
Give it to me!

21
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:50,167
No! Let me be, Logan!

22
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,367
Give it to me!

23
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,533
Emma!

24
00:01:52,667 --> 00:01:54,267
- Give it to me!
- Let me have it!

25
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,200
Give it to me! That's enough!

26
00:01:57,333 --> 00:02:00,100
Are you getting yourself
wasted for that useless man?

27
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:03,400
Come on!

28
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,500
They're blatantly
disrespecting you.

29
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:09,567
They never listen to you.

30
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:10,633
Don't you see?

31
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:13,233
He replaced you with Jade.

32
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,000
If Danilo loves you,

33
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:22,367
he won't give in to Jade
whatever she does.

34
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:26,367
Women who are being a fool for
men are no longer tolerated.

35
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,467
I'm not being a fool!

36
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,333
I'm Danilo's wife.

37
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,667
We should talk things out.

38
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:37,000
You're so stubborn.

39
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:43,167
He doesn't believe you.

40
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,900
You're married?

41
00:02:47,733 --> 00:02:52,067
When did he ever propose
marriage when you were together?

42
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:54,600
Tell me, when?

43
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:56,700
Answer me!

44
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:00,867
And when Jade proposed to him,

45
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,767
that jerk said yes without
hesitation.

46
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,267
What kind of man is that?

47
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,967
Use your brain!

48
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,700
How could Emma do this to me?

49
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:12,800
Go on, love.

50
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:15,667
Go on. Take all your anger out.

51
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,900
You have the right to do that.

52
00:03:17,933 --> 00:03:19,300
Because Emma cheated on you.

53
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,433
And with my ex, of all people.

54
00:03:22,533 --> 00:03:22,933
What?

55
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,833
That bastard is your ex?

56
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,467
Yes.

57
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,600
I was so surprised, too.

58
00:03:29,733 --> 00:03:33,333
I can't understand
how she met Logan.

59
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:34,767
But I can only think of one
reason.

60
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:39,700
Maybe Emma hates me so much that
she wants to exact revenge.

61
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,233
And she found an ally in Logan.

62
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,967
Maybe she fell in love.

63
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,767
That's why she abandoned you
and Mookie.

64
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:52,533
I hate them!

65
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:53,533
Animals!

66
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:55,933
Love, that's enough.

67
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,267
Stop being mad.

68
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:03,567
I bet that Danilo is just
putting on an act.

69
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:07,367
He blamed you before you
could confront him

70
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,633
about his infidelity.

71
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,733
And made it appear that you're
the one who cheated on him!

72
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:21,567
He'll laugh at you if you show
him any weaknesses.

73
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,067
Especially Jade!

74
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,733
Love, leave them be.

75
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:30,500
I'm sure they're enjoying
each other at this moment.

76
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:32,667
Will you let that happen?

77
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,000
Get even.

78
00:04:37,133 --> 00:04:39,033
You're right.

79
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:41,733
They're probably laughing
at me now.

80
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:45,200
Danilo and I had been
together for a long time,

81
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:48,733
but he easily replaced me
with Jade.

82
00:04:48,867 --> 00:04:51,200
He's so worthless.

83
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:59,933
And one shouldn't waste time
and tears on a worthless man.

84
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,133
Do you understand, Emma?

85
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,000
I really won't.

86
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:07,433
They can go to hell together!

87
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:09,367
That's the spirit!

88
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,867
That's the way to go, Emma!

89
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:17,933
I'll help you start again
after we get even with them.

90
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:21,333
We'll go to Singapore.

91
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:23,533
I have businesses there.

92
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:27,767
I'll make you a manager
in one of my businesses.

93
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:28,933
That's where I will...

94
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:29,967
Wait.

95
00:05:31,033 --> 00:05:31,967
What about Mookie?

96
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:34,467
I can't leave Mookie.

97
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:37,933
I can forget about Danilo.

98
00:05:38,067 --> 00:05:39,333
But I'll come back to get
Mookie.

99
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:41,200
I'll take my daughter back.

100
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,400
I'm here.

101
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,800
Emma cheated on you.

102
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:53,367
Get even with her.

103
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:04,467
I admit I felt guilty when
I stole you from Emma.

104
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:08,867
But now that I learned
she's with someone else,

105
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:12,067
and of all people, my ex?

106
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:16,700
I have nothing to feel guilty
about.

107
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,100
How did they meet?

108
00:06:22,233 --> 00:06:24,300
Does it matter?

109
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:28,733
What matters is that we know
Emma has a lover.

110
00:06:30,367 --> 00:06:31,300
My gosh,

111
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:34,900
didn't she think about you
and Mookie

112
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,767
before she had an affair?

113
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:38,367
She's a worthless mother.

114
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:42,200
She really is worthless.

115
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:42,833
Well,

116
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:49,867
Logan can provide everything
that Emma needs.

117
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,933
And even more.

118
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:53,933
Because he's filthy rich.

119
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:59,000
Emma's true colors
have finally come out.

120
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:05,600
She can easily leave you
and Mookie for money.

121
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:10,167
I can never do that
to you, Danilo.

122
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:17,133
Forget about Emma.

123
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:23,100
I'm here for you and Mookie.

124
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,367
I'll take care of you.

125
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:31,000
Promise.

126
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:33,867
After what Emma did,

127
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,967
I have no reason not
to forget her.

128
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,600
And I will never let her
get near my daughter.

129
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:23,000
You now have a great chance
on Emma, boss.

130
00:08:24,067 --> 00:08:29,000
Emma is no longer interested
in Danilo.

131
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:32,300
All that matters to her
is to get Mookie back.

132
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:37,600
I still can't be complacent,
Marco.

133
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:41,200
Emma's just angry right now.

134
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,733
But we're not sure

135
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:47,233
if she no longer has feelings
for that jerk.

136
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:53,833
I don't think Emma will
be a fool for a man.

137
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:58,300
Besides, Danilo replaced her
with Jade.

138
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:01,700
I don't think so.

139
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,100
They were together for 20 years.

140
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:09,600
It's not that easy to fall out
of love with each other.

141
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:17,333
They can reconcile if they can
talk things out.

142
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:18,333
They can get back together.

143
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:20,500
Right?

144
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:21,867
You have a point, boss.

145
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,000
What will you do now?

146
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:34,800
I'll help Emma get Mookie back.

147
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:42,167
But I'll make sure that
she never talks to Danilo again.

148
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,933
Looks like you fell in love
with Emma.

149
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:56,000
This is the first I've felt
something like this for a woman.

150
00:09:57,033 --> 00:09:59,667
Once she gets Mookie back,

151
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,333
I'll replace Danilo in their
lives.

152
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:08,700
Why don't you confess
to Emma first?

153
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:11,600
You keep helping her

154
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:15,333
but still don't know what
she feels for you.

155
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:16,067
Is that so?

156
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:17,633
Really?

157
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,733
Are you underestimating me?

158
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,700
Don't you think I can get Emma?

159
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,267
It's not like that, boss.

160
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,567
That's not what I meant.

161
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:29,667
Bastard.

162
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:31,467
Get out of my face.

163
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,733
You're ruining my night.

164
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,533
Stop drinking. That's mine!

165
00:10:50,033 --> 00:10:52,200
I saw in Danilo's eyes

166
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,733
that he still loves Emma
despite being mad.

167
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,933
He's affected by their meeting.

168
00:10:58,067 --> 00:11:03,200
<i>The way you talk makes me feel
I'm talking to Olive.</i>

169
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,700
Shut up!

170
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:07,633
It's not surprising because
Olive and I are twins.

171
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:08,900
So it's just normal for me

172
00:11:09,033 --> 00:11:10,733
to sound like her from time
to time.

173
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:17,433
Would you still be here
by now if I were Olive?

174
00:11:17,567 --> 00:11:18,433
<i> What do you mean?</i>

175
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:20,167
Hello!

176
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:23,667
You abandoned my sister.

177
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,933
You betrayed her.

178
00:11:27,067 --> 00:11:28,800
So if I were really her,

179
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:33,233
I would've taken revenge
against you.

180
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:35,333
<i> Touche.</i>

181
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:37,433
<i>You would've sent me to jail
if you were Olive.</i>

182
00:11:37,567 --> 00:11:40,967
<i>Or worse, you had me kidnapped
and thrown somewhere.</i>

183
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,267
Exactly.

184
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:44,433
Now back to the issue.

185
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:47,800
Emma can't go back
to her family.

186
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:51,967
And I'll make sure that
Mookie won't accept her, too.

187
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,900
<i> How will you do that?</i>

188
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:56,767
<i> Mookie is Emma's daughter.</i>

189
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:59,867
Danilo and I must get married
as soon as possible.

190
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:04,000
After that, I'll adopt Mookie.

191
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:06,133
So that Emma can't do anything.

192
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:11,567
Now, I need you to help me with
the wedding preparations.

193
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,500
Find me a wedding planner

194
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:17,233
who can mount a grand wedding
in three months.

195
00:12:46,367 --> 00:12:47,700
I miss you, my dear.

196
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,267
Then message her.

197
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,967
You want to get her back
from Danilo and Jade, right?

198
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:03,300
I can't do that yet.

199
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:07,467
What do you mean you can't?

200
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:10,800
Emma,

201
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,200
you're ready.

202
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:16,500
Your daughter is your weakness.

203
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:22,867
But you're ready to fight Jade
if you want to.

204
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:26,133
It's easy for you to say
because you're not in my place.

205
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:28,000
It really is easy.

206
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:31,000
You're just being a coward.

207
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:33,033
You're scared.

208
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,433
Because of Mookie.

209
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:36,467
Emma,

210
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:40,300
now is your time.

211
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:45,800
Don't be discouraged
because of your daughter.

212
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:48,967
Meet with her.

213
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,267
Tell her the truth.

214
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:55,267
Your foolish pseudo-husband
didn't listen to you,

215
00:13:56,867 --> 00:14:00,100
but your daughter might.

216
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:02,500
So,

217
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,967
what are you waiting for?

218
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:08,833
Message her.

219
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,000
Go on, Mookie.

220
00:14:21,133 --> 00:14:22,800
I know you want to rest already.

221
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:25,433
Go freshen up and change your
clothes.

222
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:35,967
I thought you blocked Zayn.

223
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,600
Why can he still message you?

224
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,200
Don't worry, baby girl.

225
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,900
Let him be.

226
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:48,200
He's not your loss if he
doesn't want you anymore.

227
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:01,567
Go on, get changed.

228
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:03,600
Good girl.

229
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,767
Is that still Zayn messaging
you?

230
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:23,733
I thought...

231
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:25,767
No, Auntie.

232
00:15:28,767 --> 00:15:29,700
It's Mom.

233
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:31,967
What?

234
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,900
She messaged me using
her private account.

235
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:40,300
So that's why we can't search
her on social media.

236
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:42,700
Her accounts are private.

237
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:45,933
It's because she's hiding.

238
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:49,600
And now that she's been caught,
she's reaching out.

239
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:50,600
What did she say?

240
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:02,900
She wanted to meet with me.

241
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:04,700
And?

242
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,333
Are you going to meet her?

243
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,533
Mookie blocked me.

244
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,567
I should've messaged her sooner.

245
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:34,100
Maybe Jade and Danilo told
her all sorts of things.

246
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:35,900
Emma,

247
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:39,867
don't give up on your daughter.

248
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:44,533
Social media isn't the only way
to talk to her.

249
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:49,933
Be courageous.

250
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:57,833
- Mooks.
- What?

251
00:16:59,467 --> 00:17:00,067
- Mooks.
- What?

252
00:17:01,267 --> 00:17:02,533
Look, I'm sorry.

253
00:17:03,567 --> 00:17:06,733
Forget everything I told you
last time.

254
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:08,333
I can't say goodbye to you.

255
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:09,233
We're friends.

256
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,900
I wish you had thought of
that before saying those things.

257
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,633
That's why I'm apologizing.

258
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:23,167
Okay, fine.

259
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:27,600
That's it?
Are you no longer mad?

260
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:29,633
Yes.

261
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:35,333
I have too many problems to even
think about our petty fight.

262
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,200
So, we're good.

263
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,667
How's Miss Emma?

264
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,767
Did you already meet?

265
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,433
I don't want to talk about her
anymore.

266
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:45,633
Sorry, sorry.

267
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,800
You're lucky I'm kind.

268
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:50,100
Thank you.

269
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:17,767
- What are you doing?
- Let me go!

270
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:19,333
Don't you dare get near
my daughter!

271
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,600
Mookie is my daughter too!

272
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,367
You don't have the right
to stop me!

273
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,900
I want to talk to her.

274
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:28,800
I won't let Mookie get
dragged into your lies too!

275
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,167
Leave us alone.

276
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:34,600
I won't stop no matter what
you do!

277
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:35,800
Emma, stop!

278
00:18:35,933 --> 00:18:37,367
Don't make a scene here!

279
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:40,167
Leave us alone!

280
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:40,833
You bastard!

281
00:18:40,967 --> 00:18:41,600
Hey!

282
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:43,733
Don't you really respect women?

283
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:45,467
Jerk.

284
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,767
Love, let's go.

285
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:49,000
Forget about them.

286
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:49,867
Let's go.

287
00:18:55,567 --> 00:18:56,167
Are you okay?

288
00:18:58,433 --> 00:18:59,300
I'm okay.

289
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,100
He's a jerk.

290
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,333
Danilo is a bastard.

291
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,467
He's closely guarding Mookie.

292
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:18,200
Why don't you just come with me
to Singapore?

293
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:21,900
What?

294
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:23,833
No.

295
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:27,100
I won't give up on Mookie.

296
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,700
Not to settle down. Relax.

297
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,300
You need a break.

298
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:35,133
You need time for yourself.

299
00:19:35,267 --> 00:19:38,100
So you can think about how you
can get Mookie back.

300
00:19:38,233 --> 00:19:39,067
No, Logan.

301
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,833
I need to act now.

302
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:45,433
I've thought of a way.

303
00:19:46,467 --> 00:19:47,167
What is it?

304
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:02,067
Hello?

305
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,367
I have a favor to ask.

306
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:13,867
Wait.

307
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,333
Why are you treating me
to a meal all of a sudden?

308
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:18,700
What's the occasion?

309
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:20,433
Hey.

310
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,200
Is it your birthday?

311
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:25,800
Is today your birthday?

312
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,567
- No. No, no, no.
- Did I forget about it?

313
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,233
It's not my birthday.

314
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,367
So what's the occasion?

315
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,167
Tell me.

316
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:34,367
Wait for it.

317
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,567
Oh, come on. You don't have
to make it suspenseful.

318
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,867
Just wait.

319
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:52,900
Mookie.

320
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:55,200
Mom?

321
00:20:57,467 --> 00:20:59,733
- Mookie, dear.
- What are you doing here?

322
00:21:04,167 --> 00:21:08,833
Zayn, did you bring me here
so we could meet?

323
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,800
Dear, don't get mad at Zayn.

324
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:15,600
I forced him to set
a meeting for us.

325
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:18,500
Sorry, Mooks,
but you need to talk.

326
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:20,100
So you can clear things out.

327
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:23,133
And ask Miss Emma
all your questions.

328
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,167
Mookie.

329
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:29,133
Can you please leave me alone?

330
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:31,967
I don't want to talk to you.

331
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:34,667
Mookie, dear.

332
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:35,833
Mookie.

333
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:39,200
I won't leave until we talk.

334
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:43,667
I can prove that they drove me
crazy in Havenwood.

335
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,467
I have the doctor's findings.

336
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,800
And I'm sure that Jade
is behind it.

337
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:51,633
I don't believe you.

338
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:53,900
Mookie, dear.

339
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:54,800
What are you doing?

340
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,467
Please hear me out first.

341
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,400
Guard.

342
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:00,300
Yes, Ma'am?

343
00:22:00,433 --> 00:22:01,900
Mister, please help me.

344
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:03,633
This woman is harassing me.

345
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:04,833
- Dear?
- Mookie?

346
00:22:04,967 --> 00:22:06,667
Dear, please. Let me explain.

347
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:07,667
Ma'am, please don't make
a scene here.

348
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:08,500
You're disturbing the customers.

349
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:09,433
It's okay, Mister.

350
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:12,233
- She's my daughter.
- No, Mister.

351
00:22:12,367 --> 00:22:13,567
- Take her away from me.
- Mookie, dear, let me...

352
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:16,300
- Hear me out first.
- This way, Ma'am.

353
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:17,567
Mookie!

354
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:19,933
- Mookie!
- This way, Ma'am.

355
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:39,000
Your daughter no longer
respects you.

356
00:22:39,133 --> 00:22:39,933
Are you still going
to chase her?

357
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,200
It's none of your business!

358
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:43,633
It is. Because I love you.

359
00:22:43,767 --> 00:22:48,233
What your mom did
is unforgivable.

360
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,300
She ruined your family.

361
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:52,667
But don't worry.

362
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,067
We can still fix this.

363
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:59,600
From now on, the three
of us will be a family.

364
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:01,600
We need to get married

365
00:23:01,733 --> 00:23:03,633
so that Emma can't do anything
anymore.

366
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:07,233
Why do you seem to push Emma
to be with Logan?

367
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:08,333
Why not?

368
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:10,133
Danilo has Jade.

369
00:23:10,267 --> 00:23:11,533
Can't Emma have Logan?

370
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:12,600
Right!

371
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:14,000
Wiro has a point.

372
00:23:14,133 --> 00:23:17,367
Congratulations!

373
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,533
What's this?

374
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:22,533
- Mookie.
- Oh my gosh, thank you!
